<topic id="14557a8c-df73-468e-9b75-56e038b79f36" revisionNumber="1">
  <developerConceptualDocument
    xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">

    <introduction>
      <para>
        Certain sections of this documentation may be marked as <quoteInline>preliminary documentation</quoteInline>.
        This page describes the role of classes and methods marked as preliminary in a release of this library.
      </para>
    </introduction>

    <section address="AddingFeatures">
      <title>Adding Features</title>
      <content>
        <para>New features SHOULD be added with the preliminary marking.</para>
        <list class="bullet">
          <listItem>
            <para>Breaking changes to features marked as preliminary are allowed in releases that do not change the assembly's strong name, provided they are listed in the release notes.</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>If any binary breaking changes were made to a feature while it was marked preliminary, the assembly strong name MUST be updated when the preliminary marking is removed. If no binary breaking changes were made to a feature while it was marked preliminary, the preliminary marking MAY be removed without changing the strong name of the assembly.</para>
          </listItem>
        </list>
      </content>
    </section>

    <section address="BreakingChanges">
      <title>Breaking Changes</title>
      <content>
        <list class="bullet">
          <listItem>
            <para>Breaking changes to binary compatibility MUST NOT be made to features without updating the assembly's strong name unless they are marked preliminary.</para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>Breaking changes to source compatibility SHOULD NOT be made to features without updating the assembly's strong name, unless they are marked preliminary.</para>
          </listItem>
        </list>
      </content>
    </section>

